PHASE 4: GAP ANALYSIS — What Our Code is Missing vs Research Requirements
==========================================================================

=== CRITICAL GAPS (Block production deployment) ===

GAP 1: No Production Inference Engine
  - Current: SignalEngine.generate() is a function call, no streaming/loop
  - Need: Persistent inference server with 5-second inference cycle
  - File to create: src/engine/inference.py
  - References: Research doc → ColossusInferenceEngine

GAP 2: No Live Sensor Integration
  - Current: Reads from pre-computed .npy files
  - Need: API connectors for NVIDIA DCGM, weather stations, Megapack SCADA
  - File to create: src/data/sensors.py
  - Interfaces: DCGM REST API, NOAA API, Tesla SCADA API

GAP 3: No Model Interpretability
  - Current: No attention visualization, no SHAP values
  - Need: Grid operator must see WHY signal was generated
  - File to create: src/engine/explain.py
  - Techniques: Attention rollout, SHAP, feature importance

=== HIGH IMPORTANCE ===

GAP 4: Sinusoidal Positional Encoding
  - Current: Learned positional params (self.pos = nn.Parameter(randn))
  - Issue: Learned positions can't extrapolate beyond training sequence length
  - Fix: Replace with sinusoidal PE in PatchEmbed or transformer.py
  - Reference: Research doc → PositionalEncoding class

GAP 5: Multi-Cluster (Global) Training
  - Current: Single cluster simulation
  - Need: Train on N data centers simultaneously → better generalization
  - Research says: Global training reduces error by 12.8-21.8%
  - File to update: src/data/generator.py (multi-cluster mode)

GAP 6: Automated Checkpoint to Drive
  - Current: Only saves best model at end
  - Need: Every 10 min auto-save + crash recovery resume
  - Colab-specific: Critical since free tier disconnects after 90 min idle

=== MEDIUM IMPORTANCE ===

GAP 7: Spike-Weighted Loss Enhancement
  - Current: Works well but no dynamic threshold adaptation
  - Research: Spike threshold = mean + 1.5*std (static)
  - Better: Adaptive threshold based on real-time grid conditions

GAP 8: Weather Nowcasting Integration
  - Current: Synthetic solar/wind only
  - Need: Real-time NOAA API + satellite imagery for cloud movement prediction
  - Long-term: Edge cameras + local vision model for 60-sec nowcasting

=== LOW IMPORTANCE (Future) ===

GAP 9: Supercapacitor Coordination Layer
  - Hardware-dependent; can be added when xAI deploys supercapacitors
GAP 10: Carbon Intensity Optimization
  - Google's approach; add when grid mix becomes relevant for xAI
